Product Description Discover the Campbell Hausfeld 20 Gallon Horizontal Air Compressor, a pinnacle of efficiency and reliability designed to meet the rigorous demands of both professional and home improvement tasks. Engineered with a robust 2 HP motor, this compressor is the epitome of power and performance, featuring dual voltage capabilities of 120/240v, making it versatile for a variety of electrical setups. This portable, single-stage compressor is equipped with a heavy-duty cast iron pump, ensuring durability and a long service life. The oil-lubricated twin cylinder pump operates smoothly, delivering an impressive 5.5 CFM at 90 PSI. With a maximum pressure of 135 PSI, it is built to handle demanding applications with ease. Whether you're inflating tires, using air tools, or conducting maintenance tasks, this compressor provides the consistent performance you need. One of the standout features of this compressor is its quiet operation, emitting only 68 dB, which makes it ideal for indoor use or environments where noise reduction is essential. The 20-gallon horizontal tank is designed for stability and ease of transport, allowing you to maneuver it effortlessly around your workspace. The Campbell Hausfeld 20 Gallon Horizontal Air Compressor is not just a tool; it is an investment in quality craftsmanship and innovation. This electric compressor is perfect for both seasoned professionals and dedicated DIY enthusiasts seeking a reliable 120v compressor solution. Enhance your home improvement projects and ensure the longevity of your tools with a compressor that stands at the forefront of technology and practicality. Trust in Campbell Hausfeld's legacy of excellence and make this compressor an integral part of your toolkit today. Amazon.com Power up pneumatic nailers, impact wrenches, ratchets and more with this beefy air compressor from Campbell Hausfeld. Wired for easy hookup to standard household current, this 20-gallon air compressor delivers enough air power to tackle all nailing jobs and works with most moderate air-tool applications. The units 20-gallon horizontal tank rolls smoothly on two large wheels for easy transport, so you can move from site to site smoothly without picking it up. A twin cylinder, oil lubricated engine offers 5 horsepower at peak output. A cast-iron, single-stage pump lets this compressor run more quietly than most compressors in its class, so running the thing close to the jobsite doesnt mean you have to wear earplugs. The cast iron design and oil lubrication also provides up to 5,000 hours of overall runtime. The unit operates on 120/240 volt service and is pre-wired for 120 volt household current. And, a fully enclosed belt guard and cooling fan keep the engine from overheating for optimal performance on extended jobs. Made in the US, the purchase is covered by a manufacturer 3-year warranty. --Brian D. Olson P.when('A').execute(function(A) {
